    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-04-29T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-04-29T20:00:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89France/292: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-29T21:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1926—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. For your own information only. Debt agreement reached today providing for
                    settlement of total debt amounting to $4,025,000,000, of which $3,340,000
                    represents principal and remainder interest accrued at four and one fourth
                    percent to December 15, 1922, and three percent thereafter to June 15, 1925.
                    Agreement provides for annuities commencing with $30,000,000 in the first year
                    and reaching $125,000,000 in the seventeenth, and thereafter at latter figure to
                    the sixty-second year. No interest for 5 years; one percent for next 10 years;
                    two percent succeeding 10 years; two and one half percent succeeding 8 years;
                    three percent succeeding 7 years, and three and one half percent for remaining
                    22 years. Present value calculated at four and one fourth percent is
                    approximately $2,000,000,000, or fifty percent of debt funded. Settlement
                    contains no safeguard clause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
